10/12/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- More than 1,000 firefighters, police and coast guard officers marched in Athens on Tuesday (9 December) to demand hazard benefits before and during the Olympics. The officers want a small financial bonus on top of their salaries and full retirement benefits for the families of those killed in the line of duty.
In other news, representatives of several human rights watchdog groups are urging Greece to improve living conditions for its population of 100,000 gypsies. The groups also urged the government to improve its treatment of illegal immigrants. (AP, Anadolu Agency, ANA - 09/12/03)
